<font color="#FF0000">MY FEAR</font><br>
<tt>Fri Oct 10 15:50:42 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Hello to you All.<br>
On this up coming Remembrance day, I will be visiting the<br>
wall for the very first time.  I am not a veteran, nor am I an American, I am a french Canadian that has been deeply been involved with a Vietnam Vet.  In the last few years that we have been together, he has gone to wall numerous times, he has visited his old friends that great him with there presence, physically they may not be there but their spirit comfort his. I am now unfortunate to say that  in the last year his health has diminished rapidly, he is a victim of Agent Orange and is greatly suffering for it, He is frightened and terrified that this may be his last visit, my frights go along with his. <br>
I have not had the chance to follow him up on his prior visits nor was I ready to do so, but this year he has asked me to accompany him; Now is the time he would like to introduce me to his friends and to experience this trip by his side.  When I heard the offer I instantly went numb to all emotions but started to cry, the thought of meeting the men that I have learned to love with out knowing, I may not have served with them but I have lived with their ghost inside on him.  <br>
Less then a month to go, and I find myself very frighten of what I will see once we get there.  We all have a past and we all have story to tell, but to come to face with what are<br>
words say for us is a very hard step to most.  I want to be with him and be his support and foundation in all this, but I am very worried that it is I that may need the support in the end.<br>
May God bless every one of you.  <br>
 
<p><code>-- lavoie@mnsi.net  (Tanya) </code><p>


